# Preferences

## Language
- Respond in French
- Code, comments, variable names, commits: in English

## General conventions
- Prefer simple and direct solutions, no over-engineering
- Do not add features that were not requested
- Do not create documentation files unless explicitly asked

## Git
- Conventional commits format: `type(scope): subject`
- Types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, perf, test, chore
- Subject: imperative, lowercase, no trailing period, max 72 characters
- GPG signed commits
- Never force push on main/master

## Security
- Never hardcode secrets, tokens, API keys

## Preferred tools
- Shell: zsh
- Editor: vim
- Terminal multiplexer: tmux
- Search: ripgrep (`rg`), not grep
- Display: bat, not cat
- Navigation: zoxide (`z`), not cd
- Fuzzy search: fzf
- Git diff: delta
- GitHub CLI: gh
- Environment: direnv (per-directory env variables)
